{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01AJFNoXUu3mB7BP2GNbHC6w","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Chess Demo\n     2→\n     3→### [▶ Play Now](https://minyic7.github.io/claude-hub-demo-chess/)\n     4→\n     5→A fully playable chess game in a single HTML file — zero dependencies, zero build step.\n     6→\n     7→Built entirely by [Claude Code](https://claude.ai).\n     8→\n     9→---\n    10→\n    11→> **Best experienced via the [live demo](https://minyic7.github.io/claude-hub-demo-chess/)** — no install required.\n    12→\n    13→## Features\n    14→\n    15→- **Complete chess rules** — all standard piece movements\n    16→- **Special moves** — castling, en passant, pawn promotion with piece selection UI\n    17→- **Check, checkmate, and stalemate detection**\n    18→- **Two-player local mode** — human vs human\n    19→- **AI opponent** — minimax search with 3–4 move lookahead\n    20→- **Play as White or Black** against the AI\n    21→- **Captured pieces display**\n    22→- **Game status display** — whose turn, check, checkmate, stalemate\n    23→- **New game button**\n    24→- **Unicode chess pieces** — no external assets needed\n    25→- **Responsive design**\n    26→\n    27→## Tech Stack\n    28→\n    29→- Single `index.html` file — all HTML, CSS, and JavaScript in one file\n    30→- Zero external dependencies\n    31→- Zero build step\n    32→- Deployed via GitHub Pages\n    33→\n    34→## Run Locally\n    35→\n    36→Open `index.html` in any browser:\n    37→\n    38→```bash\n    39→# Option 1: open directly\n    40→open index.html\n    41→\n    42→# Option 2: use a local server\n    43→python3 -m http.server\n    44→```\n    45→\n    46→## Deploy\n    47→\n    48→Push to the `main` branch — GitHub Pages auto-deploys.\n    49→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"5f6b7bca-3944-401e-b211-0aeb9e3e47a2","uuid":"abdd6250-cb23-4547-b877-7af1633d6a4f","timestamp":"2026-03-17T05:24:20.904Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/data/clones/c81b4fd9-f6b/README.md","content":"# Chess Demo\n\n### [▶ Play Now](https://minyic7.github.io/claude-hub-demo-chess/)\n\nA fully playable chess game in a single HTML file — zero dependencies, zero build step.\n\nBuilt entirely by [Claude Code](https://claude.ai).\n\n---\n\n> **Best experienced via the [live demo](https://minyic7.github.io/claude-hub-demo-chess/)** — no install required.\n\n## Features\n\n- **Complete chess rules** — all standard piece movements\n- **Special moves** — castling, en passant, pawn promotion with piece selection UI\n- **Check, checkmate, and stalemate detection**\n- **Two-player local mode** — human vs human\n- **AI opponent** — minimax search with 3–4 move lookahead\n- **Play as White or Black** against the AI\n- **Captured pieces display**\n- **Game status display** — whose turn, check, checkmate, stalemate\n- **New game button**\n- **Unicode chess pieces** — no external assets needed\n- **Responsive design**\n\n## Tech Stack\n\n- Single `index.html` file — all HTML, CSS, and JavaScript in one file\n- Zero external dependencies\n- Zero build step\n- Deployed via GitHub Pages\n\n## Run Locally\n\nOpen `index.html` in any browser:\n\n```bash\n# Option 1: open directly\nopen index.html\n\n# Option 2: use a local server\npython3 -m http.server\n```\n\n## Deploy\n\nPush to the `main` branch — GitHub Pages auto-deploys.\n","numLines":49,"startLine":1,"totalLines":49}}}
